            <p style="text-align: justify">
                Anshuman presently is on the National Science Foundation's panel that reviews small
                business and innovative research for funding by the US federal government. In this
                capacity he helps commercialize technological breakthroughs via startups.<br />
                <br />
                Previously, at ST Microelectronics, Inc., Anshuman provided leadership to $200 million
                dollar projects and new ventures in Data Encryption and Storage. He has significant
                experience leading teams spread over multiple continents since 2004 and holds a
                US patent in semiconductor design.<br />
                <br />
                Anshuman is also the co-founding President of Avlambh, Inc., a green non-profit
                with operations in US and Mexico.<br />
                <br />
                Anshuman graduated from Madan Mohan Malaviya Engg. college in 1998 with a BE in
                Electronics Engineering. He then did a Masters in Computer Science from University
                of California, Irvine and subsequently dropped out of the PhD program. He then pursued
                a Sloan Fellowship from Stanford University's Graduate School of Business.<br />
                <br />
                At Malaviya he started the I-Watch newsletter and The Malaviyan, alumni magazine.
                He was also the Chief Editor of Sanket and lead the first project in HDLs.
